Major changes:
- Install cesium and resium packages for 3D geospatial visualization
- Configure webpack to copy Cesium static assets (Workers, Widgets, etc.)
- Create route generation script that produces waypoints for ground travel
  - Supports Mapbox Directions API (when token provided)
  - Falls back to simple interpolation for development
  - Generated 10 train routes with 20+ waypoints each
- Add Cesium environment variables to .env.example
- Create CesiumViewer and CesiumViewerClient components
  - Dynamic import with no SSR (Cesium requires browser APIs)
  - Support for flight arcs and ground routes
  - Entity markers for journey events
  - Terrain support when Cesium Ion token is available

Documentation:
- Add ROUTE_DATA_REQUIREMENTS.md explaining route data format
- Document options for custom routes, waypoints, and effects
- List all 10 train journeys that need ground visualization

Next steps:
- Port full journey state management logic to Cesium
- Implement cinematic camera choreography for transitions
- Add 3D models for train/car/hiker entities
- Fetch real routes with Mapbox API
