From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Fri, 27 Feb 2026 17:30:41 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 2/3] feat(journey): create Cesium journey experience with
 camera choreography

- Implement CesiumJourneyExperience component with full state management
- Port journey timeline logic to Cesium entities and camera controls
- Add cinematic camera transitions:
  - Globe view (5M altitude) when dwelling at events
  - Low altitude follow-cam (500-700m) for ground travel (train/hike)
  - Arc camera (2-3M altitude) for flights
  - Smooth bearing calculation for directional camera
- Render journey visualization:
  - Completed flight arcs (translucent blue)
  - Active flight arcs (growing with travel progress)
  - Ground routes (terrain-hugging paths with animated entity)
  - Event markers (color-coded by status)
- Add UI overlays:
  - Event card showing current location/summary
  - Travel progress indicator
  - Bottom progress bar
  - Debug info panel
- Support wheel scroll and auto-play
- Create test route at /journey-cesium

Next: Test the visualization and refine camera movements
